Here's the working program (`Program.cs`):

```csharp
using System;
using System.Text.Json;

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions { PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase };
var json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(new Person("Jane", 30), options);
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string Name, int Age);
```

**Output:** `{"name":"Jane","age":30}`

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase` passed via `JsonSerializerOptions` — it converts PascalCase property names (`Name`, `Age`) to camelCase (`name`, `age`) during serialization.
